author: CNN
description: In a remarkable joint appearance in the Oval Office, President Donald Trump heaped praise on New York City Mayor-elect Zohran Mamdani while rejecting some GOP attacks on the democratic socialist. CNN's Kaitlan Collins analyzes what made the moment so extraordinary.
title: How Trump's meeting with Mamdani in Oval was

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump met New York City Mayor-elect Zohran Mamdani in the Oval Office today, and both called the discussion “productive.” Trump, who has previously labeled Mamdani a “communist,” said they can still collaborate on crime, housing, and New York’s cost-of-living issues.  #CNN #News
title: Trump: I think Mamdani will be 'a really great mayor'

author: CNN
description: After Democratic lawmakers published a video urging military and intelligence officials not to obey illegal orders, Trump accused them of sedition. But as CNN's Jake Tapper explains, history shows that 'just following orders' is not a legal defense. #CNN #News #Trump #Sedition
title: Trump accuses Democrats of 'sedition' but the law disagrees

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump offered praise to New York City Mayor-elect Zohran Mamdani in the Oval Office.
title: Trump says Mamdani will 'surprise' conservatives

author: CNN
description: Witchcraft, Wicca and Paganism are more popular than ever, with some estimates topping 2 million practitioners in the US. CNN's Donie O'Sullivan met with modern witches to discover what they've found in witchcraft that they haven't elsewhere. Stream the full story and watch more "Devoted" at CNN.com/allaccess
title: Inside the growing world of witchcraft in America

author: CNN
description: The Army is probing one of its largest sexual misconduct cases. Dr. Blane McGraw, a Texas Army ob/gyns called a “predator in uniform,” is accused by more than 65 women, with investigators reportedly recovering thousands of photos and videos from his phone.     #CNN #News
title: Army doctor faces allegations in widespread sexual misconduct case

author: CNN
description: Flight delays and cancellations can be stressful, but knowing your rights can help. CNN's Barry Neild explains what airlines are required to do, how to claim refunds and the best ways to stay ahead of potential disruptions.
title: Flight canceled? Here’s how to get rebooked, refunded or compensated

author: CNN
description: The Bosnian war killed roughly 100,000, displaced hundreds of thousands, and marked Europe’s deadliest atrocity since World War II. The Srebrenica genocide and Dayton Accords divided Bosnia into two NATO-monitored entities. Decades later, peace has held—prompting the question: what lessons does this diplomacy hold for today’s conflicts? CNN’s Christiane Amanpour discusses the parallels between then and now with Christopher Hill, former US Ambassador to Serbia, and Carl Bildt, former Swedish Prime Minister.     #CNN #News
title: Christiane Amanpour explores Bosnia’s diplomacy and modern conflicts

author: CNN
description: CNN's Nick Paton Walsh breaks down a new Trump administration plan for the end of the war in Ukraine. The draft plan includes a commitment that Ukraine will not join NATO, that NATO will not station troops in Ukraine, and that European fighter jets be stationed in Poland.
title: What's in the leaked Ukraine peace deal?

author: CNN
description: Researchers from the Haíɫzaqv Nation in British Columbia caught wolves possibly using tools for the first time on video. #cnn #video #science
title: Did a wolf use tools for the first time?

author: CNN
description: The dayslong immigration crackdown that arrived in Charlotte, North Carolina, last week appeared to end with the same level of confusion it began with, as local officials announced the operation concluded Thursday while federal officials refuted those claims. Meanwhile, Pope Leo weighed in on  Trump's hardline immigration enforcement saying, "we have to look for ways of treating people humanely."      #CNN #News
title: Charlotte says Border Patrol sweep is over; DHS says enforcement continues as Pope Leo weighs in

author: CNN
description:
Reporters pressed congressional Republicans about President Trump's posts that suggested Democratic lawmakers who urged service members and intelligence officials to disobey illegal orders should be put to death. Democrats on Capitol Hill have accused President Trump of trying to incite violence against them.

#CNN #News #Trump #Politics
title: GOP lawmakers respond to Trump's 'punishable by death' post

author: CNN
description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky warned Friday that Ukraine faces “one of the most difficult moments” in its history, saying a US-backed plan seen as favoring Russia would force Kyiv to sacrifice either its dignity or a vital ally.      #CNN #News
title: Zelensky cautions Trump’s path to ending war could leave Ukraine without dignity or its key US ally

author: CNN
description: White House Press Secretary Karoline Leavitt denied that President Donald Trump was calling for lawmakers to be executed, after Democrats urged service members and intelligence officials to reject illegal orders. She also argued that lawmakers with national security backgrounds shouldn’t be telling anyone to defy the administration.    #CNN #News
title: White House pushes back on claims Trump threatened to execute lawmakers

description: An Arizona family is suing ByHeart after their 4-month-old was airlifted to the hospital. The company has recalled its formula after more than 30 suspected or confirmed infant botulism cases since August, according to health officials.

author: CNN
description: In recent weeks, Israeli settler attacks and land grabs have escalated in the occupied West Bank. Under international law, Israeli settlements are considered illegal and the territory is designated as Palestinian in the eventuality of a future Palestinian state. Palestinian residents and Israeli peace activists warn the settlers' actions make that prospect more remote than ever. CNN's Nic Robertson reports. #CNN #news
title: How settlers are expanding in the West Bank

author: CNN
description: In an exclusive investigation, CNN has found evidence that Tanzanian police used deadly fire on protesters following a disputed election in October. Forensic analysis of dozens of videos and imagery reveals how protesters were killed by police and indicates mass graves concealing the scale of the brutal crackdown. CNN’s Larry Madowo reports. This report contains graphic imagery. #CNN #news
title: CNN finds evidence Tanzanian police killed protesters

author: CNN
description:
Could the secret to living longer be as simple as what’s for dinner? Sanjay sits down with Dan Buettner, author of “The Blue Zones Kitchen: One Pot Meals,” to discuss the science behind longevity, why taste (not willpower) drives healthy habits, and how affordable, plant-based recipes inspired by the world’s longest-living communities can help you thrive.

Listen to the full episode on CNN's Chasing Life podcast: http://swap.fm/l/clsgyt112125

#cnn #news #health #cooking #longevity #bluezones #bluezone #sanjaygupta #drsanjaygupta #danbuettner
title: What if comfort food could help you live to 100? | Chasing Life

description: A fire broke out inside the COP30 venue in Belém, Brazil, before it was brought under control. Electrical equipment, likely a microwave, is believed to have caused the blaze, according to a Reuters report citing local officials. #CNN #News #COP30
title: Video shows fire break out at COP30

author: CNN
description: Congressional Delegate Stacey Plaskett texted with Jeffrey Epstein while sitting in a congressional hearing with President Trump’s former lawyer, Michael Cohen, in 2019. The texts were first reported by The Washington Post. Documents recently released by the House Oversight Committee show that Plaskett and Epstein were coordinating, in real time, about questions Plaskett would ask Cohen. CNN’s Annie Grayer reports. #cnn #news
title: House Democrat texted with Epstein during congressional hearing

description: Federal officials unveiled additional charges on Wednesday against a former Olympic snowboarder for Canada who has been wanted for allegedly running a drug trafficking ring. The new charges against Ryan James Wedding include murder, witness tampering, money laundering and drug trafficking, Attorney General Pam Bondi said at news conference.
title: New charges against former Olympic athlete accused of running drug ring
